25 (1) death; or
26 (2) bodily injury that gives a law enforcement officer reason to
27 believe that the death of at least one (1) person is imminent.
28 (c) As used in this chapter, "roadside chemical test" means a
29 portable chemical test that can be administered by the side of a
30 road.
